        • [ - ] SteveHyland - member since 03-Nov-12

          @neumi17- I think it's more to do with the fact Pep teams can only play one way. At the Nou Camp, Allianz or Etihad that's fine because unless they face a team as good as they are (in pure footballing terms), it's unlikely anyone will go there looking to force the issue- most will happily sit back and look for counter opportunities (even some good teams will do this). When a team is at home, however, with their own fans expecting and the team themselves thinking they should be aggressive either in terms of tactics or physicality, Pep's plan A can be laid to waste. He doesn't have a plan B, he is a purist to it's core, so against a fired-up team who have very little to lose and playing at home, you can get results contrary to that expected given the relative abilities of the XIs on show.

          3 years ago
